SIMPLE: infringe
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Infringe
<hw>In*fringe"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Infringed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Infringing</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>infringere</ets>; pref. <ets>in-</ets> in + <ets>frangere</ets> to
break. See <er>Fraction</er>, and cf. <er>Infract</er> .]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To break; to violate; to transgress; to neglect to
fulfill or obey; <as>as, to <ex>infringe</ex> a law, right, or
contract</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If the first that did the edict <qex>infringe</qex>,⟦br⟧
Had answered for his deed.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The peace . . . was <qex>infringed</qex> by Appius Claudius.</q>
<rj><qau>Golding.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To hinder; to destroy; <as>as, to <ex>infringe</ex>
efficacy; to <ex>infringe</ex> delight or power.</as></def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Hooker.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Infringe</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Infringe
<hw>In*fringe"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To break,
violate, or transgress some contract, rule, or law; to injure; to
offend.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To encroach; to trespass; -- followed by
<xex>on</xex> or <xex>upon</xex>; <as>as, to <ex>infringe</ex> upon the
rights of another</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Infringement</ent>⟦br⟧
